All Classes

  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Alarm
    This class is use to model an alarm as records in the database
    AlarmBroadcastReceiver
    This class handles the broadcast from the AlarmManager.
    AlarmDao
    This interface provide methods that your app can use to query, update, insert, and delete data in the database.
    AlarmDatabase
    This class serves as the base class for all Room databases.
    AlarmRecyclerViewAdapter
    This class contains Adapter and ViewHolder.
    AlarmRepository
    This is class is used to retrieve Alarm records from the Room database
    AlarmService
    The service will run in the foreground and display a notification while playing a looping alarm sound and a looping vibration pattern.
    AlarmsListFragment
    This class displays all of the Alarms in a RecyclerView, which includes information about the Alarm timings, the alarm title, whether it is repeating or not, which days of the week the alarm will sound, and a Toggle that indicates whether the alarm is active or not.
    AlarmsListViewModel
    This class uses the AlarmRepository and the Room database to locate the alarms and is used by the AlarmsListFragment to retrieve the Alarm records to show in the RecyclerView.
    AlarmViewHolder
    This class displays or binds the records from the database to the user Interface
    App
    This class is used to implement a notification channel.
    DayUtil
    Class that returns String of the Day
    MainActivity
    This is the Main Activity
    OnManageListener
    This interface listener checks whether the alarm is active or not, for checking if the user clicks the delete icon or click the item alarm layout.
    RescheduleAlarmsService
    This class reschedule any alarms that were cancelled when the device was booted
    RingActivity
    The Ring activity class will be displayed only if the user picks the push notification displayed when an alarm is active.
    ScheduleAlarmActivity
    Binds the fragment for ScheduleAlarm since it is going to be reused during updating an alarm
    ScheduleAlarmFragment
    This class follows the MVVM design pattern to insert instances of the Alarm model into the Room Database via a ViewModel and a Repository when a user captures submits a new alarm
    ScheduleAlarmViewModel
    This class is used to call the insert method on the AlarmRepository and passes the Alarm.
    SplashScreen
    The splash screen can be displayed at application startup, The splash screen is displayed as an undecorated window containing an image.
    TimePickerUtil
    final class for checking the API level(since before android 6-Marshmallow, the methods where getCurrentHour() and getCurrentMinute() rather than the getHour() and getMinute() now as well as their setter methods)
